text: The 1993 NCAA Division I Men's Swimming and Diving Championships were contested in March 1993 at the Indiana University Natatorium in Indianapolis, Indiana at the 70th annual NCAA-sanctioned swim meet to determine the team and individual national champions of Division I men's collegiate swimming and diving in the United States. The men's and women's titles would not be held at the same site until 2006. Stanford again topped the team standings, finishing 124.5 points ahead of Michigan.
